    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-14T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-14T23:00:00-05:00" n="1054"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1054">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Winterle/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-15T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 15, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 15—6
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Embassy’s 52, October 12, 9 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m.<note n="91"
                        xml:id="d1054fn91">Not printed.</note> Following telegram has been received
                    from Chefoo.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“October 14, 5 p.m. Following from Ballantine: At interview with the Japanese
                        Consul he rejected our proposed basis of settlement and reaffirmed his
                        previous proposal. Full report by mail. I see no advantage in continuing
                        discussions and propose returning to Mukden October 15, 5 p.m. unless
                        otherwise instructed.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>The proposed basis of settlement mentioned by Ballantine was set forth in the
                    Embassy’s 34, October 7, 3 p.m.</p>
                <pb facs="1208" n="1096" xml:id="pg_1096"/>
                <p>In view of Ballantine’s report I propose to take no further action in the matter
                    unless fresh overtures are made by the Japanese authorities. If mail report from
                    Ballantine contains new information which alters the situation the Department
                    will be informed.</p>
                <p>I am authorizing Ballantine to return to Mukden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
